org.openimaj.feature.local

Interface LocalFeature<L extends Location,T extends FeatureVector>

  • Type Parameters:
    L - The type of Location
    T - The type of FeatureVector
    All Superinterfaces:
    FeatureVectorProvider<T>, LocalFeatureVectorProvider<L,T>, LocationProvider<L>, Readable, ReadableASCII, ReadableBinary, ReadWriteable, Writeable, WriteableASCII, WriteableBinary
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AffineInterestPointKeypoint, AffineSimulationKeypoint, ByteDSIFTKeypoint, CircularInterestPointKeypoint, FloatDSIFTKeypoint, FloatKeypoint, FloatLocalFeatureAdaptor, InterestPointKeypoint, Keypoint, LocalFeatureImpl, MinMaxKeypoint, QuantisedAffineSimulationKeypoint, QuantisedKeypoint, QuantisedLocalFeature, SIFTGeoKeypoint

    public interface LocalFeature<L extends Location,T extends FeatureVector>
extends ReadWriteable, LocalFeatureVectorProvider<L,T>
    A LocalFeature models a feature that has a Location associated with it. Local features are ReadWriteable, and also implement LocalFeatureVectorProvider so that the Location and FeatureVector can be easily obtained.
    Author:
    Jonathon Hare (jsh2@ecs.soton.ac.uk)
